ğŸš€ TaskFlow â€“ Project & Task Management API (Django + DRF)

TaskFlow is a clean, modular backend API for managing projects, members, boards, columns, tasks, comments, and labels â€” inspired by tools like Trello or Linear.
It is built using Django 5, Django REST Framework, and JWT Authentication.

âœ¨ Features
ğŸ” Authentication

JWT-based authentication (login / signup)

Custom user model

ğŸ“ Projects

Create / Update / Delete projects

Project ownership system

Members management with roles:

OWNER

ADMIN

MEMBER

Only allowed users can access or modify project content

ğŸ‘¥ Project Members

Invite new members by username

Update member roles

Remove members (except OWNER)

Permission handling for all operations

ğŸ“Š Boards & Columns

Each project contains multiple boards

Each board contains multiple columns

Columns are orderable (supports drag & drop behavior)

ğŸ“ Tasks

Create / update / delete tasks

Assign tasks to users

Priority levels: LOW, MEDIUM, HIGH

Due dates

Completion state

Orderable inside columns (drag & drop support)

Move tasks across columns

ğŸ’¬ Comments

Add comments to tasks

Only authors can edit or delete their own comments

Comment list & detail endpoints

ğŸ·ï¸ Labels / Tags (New Feature)

Create labels for each project

Set label color (HEX value)

Assign multiple labels to a task

Filter tasks by labels

Only project members can manage labels

ğŸ” Task Filtering & Search

The API supports advanced filtering:

Parameter	Description
project	Filter by project ID
column	Filter by column ID
assignee	Username of task assignee
priority	low / medium / high
is_complete	true / false
q	Search in title & description
due_before	Filter by deadline upper bound
due_after	Filter by deadline lower bound
ğŸ§± Tech Stack

Python 3.12+

Django 5

Django REST Framework

SimpleJWT

SQLite / PostgreSQL

ğŸ“¦ Installation
git clone https://github.com/ashkanhajian/taskflow
cd taskflow

python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

pip install -r requirements.txt

âš™ï¸ Running the Project
python manage.py migrate
python manage.py runserver


The API will start at:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/

ğŸ”‘ Authentication Endpoints
Method	Endpoint	Description
POST	/api/auth/register/	Register a new user
POST	/api/auth/login/	Get JWT access token
POST	/api/auth/refresh/	Refresh JWT token
ğŸ“ Main API Structure
/api/projects/                         â†’ Create & list projects
/api/projects/<id>/                    â†’ Retrieve, update, delete project
/api/projects/<id>/members/            â†’ List & add members
/api/projects/<id>/members/<pk>/       â†’ Update & delete member

/api/boards/                           â†’ Boards list/create
/api/columns/                          â†’ Columns list/create
/api/tasks/                            â†’ Tasks list/create

/api/tasks/<id>/                       â†’ Update / delete task
/api/tasks/<id>/comments/              â†’ Task comments
/api/labels/                           â†’ Label list/create
/api/labels/<id>/                      â†’ Label detail

